<pre><code>#include&lt;iostream&gt;  int&amp; reference(){    int i = 100;    return i; }  int main(){    int&amp; x = reference();    std::cout&lt;&lt;x;    return 0; } </code></pre>  <p>Upto my level of understanding reference function will return the reference of i. But the scope of i is inside the function only. I want to ask </p>  <p>(1) whether x is referring to the same i.<br> (2) what happens to local variable i after the function returns reference to the integer.</p>